userFeatureClass.name: Shaded
userFeatureClass.documentation: a number between 0 and 100 expressing 100 for shaded and 0 for sunny

variableClass.name: LevelOfCleanness
variableClass.documentation: variable expressing the level of cleanness as a number between 0 and 100 with 100 being totally clean

variableClass.name: maxNoUsers
variableClass.documentation: This variable describes how many agents may use this resource at the same time under the assumption that agents will keep a certain minimal distance at all times. The minimal distance is a variable provided in the world (because the number changes with the environmental scale). The default value is a calculation of largest dimension of object divided by 1.2 * size of the agent (determined in world). 1.2 is used as a "buffer" between agents. This could be replaced by Hall's spaces.

variableClass.name: collision_shape
variableClass.documentation: This shape is a Buffershape with the factor 1.2 (i.e. 20% larger than original shape) that is being used for collision calculation.

variableClass.name: height[m]
variableClass.documentation: The height of a resource is of importance to the potential interactions. The default value is 0 due to the many groundtiles.

variableClass.name: size_light_circle
variableClass.documentation:
size of light circle depends on the hight of the light source and is calculated using the (simplified) formula

height x 1,5 [m]

This assumes that the light source has an angle of reflected beam of about 110 degrees.

The full formula would be

TAN (angle/2) * height

angle in radians, i.e. angle * pi / 180
